function [CPO] = cpi2cpo(CPI,imagesize,objectsize)% function [CPO] = cpi2cpo(CPI,imagesize,objectsize)%% Converts cycles per image [CPI] into cycles per object [CPO].% This is just when the object size is not equal to the field% upon which it is being presented.%% March 23, 1997.  JMG  PJB  ABS   U of Toronto Vision LabCPO = CPI*(objectsize/imagesize);return